It\'s never dark or light
Grey Stories

Laura has passed through a lot. She encounters herself alone, sad and watching hopelessly the street through her window. Soon after, she jumps out of it. Just at that moment, she hears a sound and regrets jumping. What could happen?

Tom is known as a survivor. After a really traumatic situation, he appeared in the news, talk shows and different interviews. To commemorate the event, he decides to go to a restaurant, the only one where they serve that specific meal, a Seagull Soup. He tries a bit, but just after the first sip of soup, he comes back to his house and dies. The soup was not poisonous, so why was it his last meal?
After a huge fire in a large forest, a burned diver is found right in the middle of it. How on Earth did he get there?!
When Victor was coming back to his house on his bike, a car ran over him. When the policeman arrived, the driver did not get arrested, but someone else. Who and why?
Paula was just waking up. The sun was shining through the window. She stretches and looks through it when she sees a really majestic bird. Soon after, she knows she is about to die. Why?
They were the best dancing couple in the competition. Everyone was enjoying the dance, but suddenly, in the last dance move, the girl falls dead to the ground. What could happen?
Bruno goes to his routine check-up. When he’s coming back to his house, he witnesses a kidnapping. When he tells the police, they do not believe him. How outraging! Why they don’t believe him?!

A girl has always wanted to open the cellar door, however, she was warned by her parents not to open it. One day, while her parents were out, they accidentally left the cellar door unlocked. The girl opened the cellar door and started crying. What did she see?
Lily is an assistant. She tries a new pair of shoes, goes to work, and dies. What could have happened?
A hunter aimed his gun carefully and fired. Seconds later, he realized his mistake. Minutes later, he was dead. What was his mistake?
A man went into a party and drank some of the punch. He then left early. Everyone at the party who drank the punch then died of poisoning. Why did the man not die?

John works in an agency. After a long day at work, he gets home and watches the news. One of the news was of a girl that died while vacationing with his boyfriend. Everyone believes it was an accident, but John knows the boyfriend is lying. What does he know about that?
Francis dies of a heart attack at work. His colleagues are there when it happens. However, they do not call for help until Francis dies. Why would they wait for so long?
A man is walking when he suddenly sees a cactus and notices an empty sheet of paper on it. He lies down and starts crying. Why?

If the player is lost, here are some questions they can ask!


- Was she alone?

- Were people on the streets?

- Did the sound come from a radio?

- Did Tom have any disability?

- Did he get in a lifeboat?

- Was he alone in the lifeboat?

- Did someone from his family died?

- Was the man in the water before getting on the plane?

After a world catastrophe, Laura thought that she was the only person alive and decided to jump out of her window. When radio sounded, she realized someone was talking through the radio and she was not alone, but it was too late for her.

Tom, a blind man, was on a ship with his brother enjoying their holidays. Unfortunately, there was a shipwreck and Tom had to escape from the ship with his brother. They got into a lifeboat with their friend, a chef. After days of navigating without direction, they started to starve. As Tom was blind, the chef decided to kill his brother in order to eat him and gave a plate to Tom, telling him that it was seagull soup. Tom survived thinking that his brother died of starvation, but when he commemorated the event and tried an actual seagull soup, he realized he didn’t eat seagull, but his brother. Helpless and outraged, he went home to die.

Paul, the unlucky man, was diving in a large lake close to the forest. When the fire started, a plane started taking water from the lake to extinguish the fire. Paul was caught by the plane and thrown over the fire.

The driver was receiving driving lessons and his instructor told him to turn in the wrong direction, crashing into a bike. The policemen considered the driving instructor to be responsible for the accident.
Paula was a passenger in an aircraft. The bird flew into the engine, making the airplane crash to the ground.
It was a tango competition. Another couple, who were very competitive, poisoned a rose and gave it to them. In the last dance move, the girl smelled the rose, dying in the act.
It was a dentist\'s check-up. After leaving the dentist, Bruno was not able to speak properly as he had a numb mouth. The police thought he was drunk and did not take the story seriously.
When the girl opened the cellar door she saw the house garden. She had never seen it before because her parents had kept her in the cellar all her life.

Lily was the assistant to a circus knife-thrower, who stands in front of a target as knives are thrown around her. The new shoes have higher heels than she normally wears, causing the thrower to misjudge his aim.
He hunted in snowed mountains. The shot provoked an avalanche, which covered the man. He died of suffocation.

The poison from the punch came from the ice cubes. When the man drank the punch, the ice was fully frozen. He had to leave early for an emergency and was lucky. Gradually, as the ice cubes melted the poison was released into the punch.

The man is a travel agent. One day, a guy approached and asked for two tickets, one round-trip and one one-way. Although it looked weird to John, he sold the tickets. When he saw the news, he realized that guy was her boyfriend, and he killed her.

Francis was a theatre actor and suffered a heart attack in the middle of a performance. However, he was playing someone who was having a heart attack. Therefore, both his colleagues and the audience simply thought that he was giving a really impressive performance.
The man was lost in a desert and it was his own sheet of paper, which he left when he wandered through the desert. When he saw it, he realized that he\'s been lost for so long.

Hey there!

My name is Pablo Sanchez. I am a Software engineering student. This is my first Android application, I hope you enjoy it!
If you find any bugs/errors, please email me at sanchezn.pabloalejandro@gmail.com.
Grey Stories is an adaptation of Dark Stories\nEnjoy it with friends!
One person, chosen as a narrator, picks a story and reads its description to the rest of the group

The narrator reads the solution without telling the rest of the players. Then, the players have to make questions to solve the story. These should be Yes/No questions. The narrator can ONLY reply:\nYES/NO/IRRELEVANT
And that\'s it! Now enjoy with your friends and let\'s see who is the best detective!

Let’s make a community!
If you want your story to appear on this app, send it over to me via email. I will give you full credits and your socials will appear on the screen!


This application uses Android Studio, Java and Xml.


Grey Stories 1.0.0
In the middle of the ocean, there is a large yacht. Several corpses are floating in the water nearby. What happened?

If the player is lost, here are some questions they can ask!


- Was it the people’s fault?

- Was the yacht tall?

A group of people were on an ocean voyage on a yacht. One day, they decided to go swimming. They put on their swimsuits and dove off the side. They discovered belatedly that they have forgotten to put a ladder down the side of the yacht and were unable to climb back in, so they drowned.

John was walking along the snow-covered field. When he came to a lonely tree, he saw the corpse of a man hanging on the tree. He died last night from strangulation, but there were no traces around him, except John\'s ones. This is weird…
The hanged man was a skydiver. His parachute was entangled and caught on branches of the tree.

If the player is lost, here are some questions they can ask!


- Did the man do it on purpose?

- Was the man standing on the floor before the incident?
